%% Agent Studio Desktop P2 — Sequence Diagrams
%% Key workflows: startup, streaming, migration bridge, settings CRUD

sequenceDiagram
    participant HTML as index.html
    participant Main as main.tsx
    participant Providers
    participant App as App.tsx
    participant Store as Zustand Stores
    participant Query as React Query
    participant API as api.ts
    participant WS as websocket.ts
    participant Page as Page Component
    participant Backend

    title 🚀 1. Application Startup Flow (Phase 2a)

    HTML->>Main: <script type="module" src="/src/app/main.tsx">
    Main->>Main: import Providers, App, stores, i18n
    Main->>Providers: ReactDOM.createRoot(document.getElementById('root'))
    Main->>Store: useAppStore.getState().set('connectionStatus', 'connecting')
    Main->>API: healthCheck()
    API->>Backend: GET /health
    Backend-->>API: 200 OK
    API-->>Main: true
    Main->>Store: set('connectionStatus', 'connected')
    Main->>Providers: render <Providers><App /></Providers>
    Main->>App: mount

    App->>Store: useAppStore() → subscribe to state
    App->>App: BrowserRouter setup
    App->>App: render AppShell (TopBar + Sidebar + TabBar + <Outlet/>)

    par Parallel Data Loading (React Query)
        Query->>API: useConversationsQuery() → GET /api/conversations
        API->>Backend: fetch
        Backend-->>API: conversations[]
        API-->>Query: normalized data
        Query-->>App: conversations in cache

        Query->>API: useAgentsQuery() → GET /api/agents
        API->>Backend: fetch
        Backend-->>API: agents[]
        API-->>Query: agents in cache

        Query->>API: useProvidersQuery() → GET /api/providers
        API->>Backend: fetch
        Backend-->>API: providers[]
        API-->>Query: providers in cache
    end

    App->>WS: websocket.connect()
    WS->>Backend: ws://127.0.0.1:25808/ws
    Backend-->>WS: connected
    WS-->>App: emit('connected')
    App->>Store: set('connectionStatus', 'connected')

    App-->>HTML: 🟢 Application Ready

    === 💬 2. Streaming Message Flow (Phase 2c) ===

    actor User
    participant Input as MessageInput
    participant Hook as useChatStream
    participant Buf as useRef Buffer
    participant Text as StreamingText
    participant MsgList as MessageList
    participant ChatStore as useChatStore
    participant Backend

    title 💬 2. Streaming Message Rendering Flow

    User->>Input: type message + press Enter
    Input->>Input: validate text
    Input->>ChatStore: setGenerating(true)
    Input->>API: sendMessage(convId, { text, mode, model, expert, skills })
    API->>Backend: POST /api/conversations/:id/messages
    Backend-->>API: { success: true }

    Note over Backend,WS: Streaming via WebSocket

    loop For each chunk
        Backend->>WS: { name: 'message.chunk', data: { messageId, content } }
        WS->>Hook: on('message.chunk', callback)
        Hook->>Buf: bufferRef.current.set(messageId, accumulated + chunk)
        Hook->>Hook: cancelAnimationFrame(rafId)
        Hook->>Hook: rafId = requestAnimationFrame(flush)
    end

    Note over Hook: rAF fires (next frame, ~16ms)

    Hook->>Buf: accumulated = bufferRef.current.get(messageId)
    Hook->>ChatStore: useChatStore.setState({ streamContent: accumulated })
    Hook->>Buf: bufferRef.current.set(messageId, '')
    ChatStore-->>Text: re-render with new content
    Text->>Text: dangerouslySetInnerHTML (sanitized via DOMPurify)
    Text->>MsgList: auto-scroll to bottom

    Backend->>WS: { name: 'message.done', data: { messageId } }
    WS->>Hook: on('message.done')
    Hook->>Buf: final flush
    Hook->>ChatStore: setGenerating(false)
    Hook->>Query: invalidateQueries(['messages', convId])
    Query->>API: refetch messages
    API-->>Query: full message list
    Query-->>MsgList: re-render complete message

    === 🔗 3. Progressive Migration Bridge (Phase 2a-2c) ===

    participant OldJS as Old JS Component
    participant Window as window (event bus)
    participant Store
    participant ReactComp as React Component

    title 🔗 3. Old JS ↔ React Bridge Flow

    Note over OldJS,ReactComp: Phase 2a-2c: both systems coexist

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over OldJS,ReactComp: OLD → REACT direction

        OldJS->>OldJS: state.set('currentPage', 'settings')
        OldJS->>Window: window.__AGENT_STUDIO_STORE__ = useAppStore
        OldJS->>Window: window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('app:page-changed', { detail: { page: 'settings' } }))

        Window->>ReactComp: useEffect listens to 'app:page-changed'
        ReactComp->>Store: useAppStore.setState({ currentPage: 'settings' })
        Store-->>App: re-render Router → SettingsPage
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over OldJS,ReactComp: REACT → OLD direction

        ReactComp->>Store: user clicks "Open Settings" button
        Store-->>App: Router navigates to /settings
        App->>Window: window.dispatchEvent(new CustomEvent('app:route-changed', { detail: { path: '/settings' } }))

        Window->>OldJS: old code can react to route change
        OldJS->>OldJS: close legacy panels, update UI
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over OldJS,ReactComp: Phase 2d: bridge removed
        Note over OldJS,ReactComp: Old JS files deleted; React is sole source of truth
    end

    === ⚙️ 4. Settings CRUD Flow (React Query + Optimistic Update) ===

    actor User
    participant SettingsUI as SettingsPage
    participant Mutation as useUpdateSettings
    participant QueryCache as React Query Cache
    participant API
    participant Backend
    participant Toast

    title ⚙️ 4. Settings Save Flow (Optimistic Update)

    User->>SettingsUI: toggle "自动保存" switch
    SettingsUI->>Mutation: mutate({ autoSave: true })
    Mutation->>Mutation: onMutate: cancel in-flight queries
    Mutation->>QueryCache: snapshot = getQueryData(['settings'])
    Mutation->>QueryCache: setQueryData(['settings'], optimistic)
    Mutation-->>SettingsUI: ✅ switch toggles immediately (optimistic)

    Mutation->>API: PATCH /api/settings { autoSave: true }
    API->>Backend: HTTP PATCH
    Backend-->>API: { success: true, data: { autoSave: true } }
    API-->>Mutation: response

    alt Success
        Mutation->>QueryCache: invalidateQueries(['settings'])
        QueryCache->>API: refetch in background
        API-->>QueryCache: latest settings
        QueryCache-->>SettingsUI: consistent state
        Mutation->>Toast: show('设置已保存', 'success')
    else Error
        Mutation->>QueryCache: setQueryData(['settings'], snapshot)
        QueryCache-->>SettingsUI: ⚡ rollback to previous state
        Mutation->>Toast: show('保存失败', 'error')
    end

    === 🌙 5. Theme Toggle Flow (MUI + Tailwind CSS Variable Bridge) ===

    participant Toggle as ThemeToggle
    participant ThemeStore as useThemeStore
    participant Document as document.documentElement
    participant MUIProvider as MUI ThemeProvider

    title 🌙 5. Theme Toggle Flow

    User->>Toggle: click theme toggle
    Toggle->>ThemeStore: useThemeStore.getState().toggleTheme()
    ThemeStore->>ThemeStore: newTheme = current === 'dark' ? 'light' : 'dark'
    ThemeStore->>Document: setAttribute('data-theme', newTheme)
    Note over Document: CSS variables change:<br/>--color-bg → #0d0d0d<br/>--color-fg → #ffffff
    ThemeStore->>MUIProvider: createTheme({ palette: { mode: newTheme } })
    MUIProvider-->>Toggle: all MUI components re-render with new palette
    ThemeStore->>ThemeStore: localStorage.setItem('agent-studio-theme', newTheme)
